In a meeting with members of the Cuban American community, President Biden discussed the United States' support for the Cuban people who have suffered under the communist regime. He acknowledged the recent demonstrations in Cuba and condemned the regime's response of violence and repression. The United States is taking action by imposing sanctions on individuals and entities involved in suppressing protesters. The administration is also working to provide Internet access to the Cuban people to bypass censorship and increase support for political prisoners and dissidents. President Biden has directed the State Department and Treasury Department to provide recommendations on maximizing remittances to the Cuban people without benefiting the Cuban military. The administration aims to increase U.S. staffing at the embassy while prioritizing personnel safety. The President emphasized the importance of listening to the ideas and expertise of the Cuban American community. He stated that unless there is a significant change in Cuba, more sanctions will be imposed.